cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

The paper presents a method to compress neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning research. The use of differentiable pruning functions and a new regularizer specifically designed to enforce pruning suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The fact that the proposed method is evaluated on recognition tasks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of neural networks and the focus on compression suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the analysis of the generalization capabilities of the pruned network suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
